		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Remember back when they changed it so that mobs could walk through walls?  There was a certain place, not sure which, where there were NPC's that were behind locked doors.  I think the idea was that you were supposed to get a rogue to unlock it for you.  People would attack the NPC, and it would open the door and come out to get them, so they were getting the door opened for &quot;free.&quot;  So, they changed it so that the NPC would just walk right through the wall.  Anybody else remember when this happened? <br>  <br> So, if the mob was opening the door before, collision detection is already in place, and was so for over a year.  It can't be a problem with collision detection taking too much CPU time.  The main reason, I think, is as others have already said; it makes it so the monster can get right too you as quick as possible and kill you.  It's the same reason that monsters will teleport on top of you if they get too far behind, but if your computer slows down, you will just stand there while they catch you.<p>

							

